Signaling Explainer

Jeffrey A. Walker

2023-06-01

Nervous, endocrine, paracrine, and autocrine are four types of signaling

  • there are alternative classification systems. They all include endocrine, paracrine and autocrine. Chemical synapses in nervous signaling is a special case of paracrine.

Plasma membrane receptors bind hydrophilic signals. Intracellular receptors bind lipophilic signals

Signal transduction includes all of the events from signal binding to cell response
